# Cursor Rules — LinkDeck

## Project
LinkDeck is a Chrome Extension (Manifest V3) — a configurable new-tab dashboard with Chrome Tab Groups. Vanilla JS + ES modules, Vite build, Vitest tests, ESLint.

## Hard Rules
- No frameworks (React, Vue, etc.) — vanilla JS only.
- No external YAML libraries — `parser.js` is hand-written on purpose.
- No `chrome.storage.sync` — use `chrome.storage.local` only.
- No hardcoded colors in CSS — use design tokens (custom properties).
- Never edit `src/icon-data.js` by hand — it is auto-generated.
- Always run `npm run lint && npm test` before finishing.

## Code Style
- ES modules (`import`/`export`), `const` by default, `let` if needed, no `var`.
- ESLint flat config. `no-unused-vars` = warning; prefix unused params with `_`.
- Test files: `src/*.test.js` colocated with source. Framework: Vitest.
- Chrome APIs and DOM are unavailable in tests — guard with `typeof`.
- Comments in German or English are fine.

## Architecture
```
src/newtab.js       — Dashboard rendering + Tab Groups + Spotlight search
src/options.js      — WYSIWYG editor + YAML editor + backup
src/parser.js       — YAML parse + normalize + serialize (hand-written)
src/search-engines.js — Search engine presets + storage helpers
src/icon-picker.js  — Material Icons picker (4176 icons, 17 category tabs)
src/icon-data.js    — AUTO-GENERATED icon DB (do not touch)
src/background.js   — Service worker (context menu)
src/theme.js        — Light/system/dark toggle
src/styles.css      — Design tokens + responsive (640px / 1024px)
```

## Config Schema
Groups → Sections → Links. Chrome color enum: grey|blue|red|yellow|green|pink|purple|cyan|orange.
Storage keys: `yamlText`, `searchEngine`, `searchBarVisible`, `yamlBackups`.

## Commands
```bash
npm run dev          # Dev server
npm run build        # Production → dist/
npm run lint         # ESLint
npm test             # Vitest (73 tests)
```
